This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with personalized recommendations and their effect on user engagement and content consumption. It could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD) sub-categories as it involves analyzing user behavior on a music streaming platform. Additionally, the paper touches upon issues related to user privacy and algorithmic bias, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of personalized recommendations on user retention and lifetime value, which could be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
